The paper focuses on developing an alternative approach to building static analysis tools for detecting vulnerabilities in web applications. The approach involves using artificial intelligence concepts, specifically natural language processing, to train a sequence model to automatically detect flaws in the program source code. This makes it likely that the paper would be classified under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper deals with security vulnerabilities, which could place it under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves processing programming languages, which could place it under cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the use of artificial intelligence concepts suggests that the paper could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
